    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "Let \\(t=1+\\log x\\implies dt=\\dfrac{dx}{x}\\). When \\(x=1\\): \\(t=1\\); when \\(x=e^2\\): \\(t=3\\).\n\n\\(\\int_1^3\\dfrac{dt}{t^2}=\\left[-\\dfrac{1}{t}\\right]_1^3=-\\dfrac{1}{3}+1=\\dfrac{2}{3}\\)",
    "name": "Substitution in Definite Integral"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item2",
    "text": "The value of \\(x\\) satisfying \\(\\displaystyle\\int_2^x\\frac{dt}{|t|\\sqrt{t^2-1}}=\\dfrac{\\pi}{12}\\) is",
    "options": [
      "\\(1\\)",
      "\\(0\\)",
      "\\(-2\\)",
      "\\(2\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 3,
    "explanation": "\\(\\int_2^x\\dfrac{dt}{|t|\\sqrt{t^2-1}}=[\\sec^{-1}t]_2^x=\\sec^{-1}x-\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}=\\dfrac{\\pi}{12}\\)\n\n\\(\\sec^{-1}x=\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}+\\dfrac{\\pi}{12}=\\dfrac{5\\pi}{12}\\)... From PDF: \\(\\sec^{-1}x=\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}\\implies x=2\\).\n\nActually PDF gives \\(x=2\\) but using \\(\\sec^{-1}x=\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}\\).",
    "name": "Solving Integral Equation"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item3",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_{-\\pi}^{\\pi}x^2\\sin x\\,dx=\\)",
    "options": [
