      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi^2}{2}\\)",
      "\\(0\\)",
      "\\(2\\pi^2\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "\\(f(x)=x^2\\sin x\\). Since \\(f(-x)=(-x)^2\\sin(-x)=-x^2\\sin x=-f(x)\\), the function is **odd**.\n\n\\(\\int_{-\\pi}^{\\pi}x^2\\sin x\\,dx=0\\)",
    "name": "Odd Function Integral Over Symmetric Interval"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item4",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^1\\sin^{-1}\\frac{2x}{1+x^2}\\,dx=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(\\pi-\\log2\\)",
      "\\(\\pi+\\log2\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}-\\log2\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}+\\log2\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "Let \\(x=\\tan\\theta\\), limits \\(0\\to\\pi/4\\):\n\n\\(I=\\int_0^{\\pi/4}2\\theta\\sec^2\\theta\\,d\\theta\\). By IBP:\n\n\\(=2[\\theta\\tan\\theta-\\log|\\sec\\theta|]_0^{\\pi/4}=2\\left(\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}-\\dfrac{1}{2}\\log2\\right)=\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}-\\log2\\)",
    "name": "Definite Integral via Trig Substitution"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item5",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^1\\frac{8\\log(1+x)}{1+x^2}\\,dx=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(\\pi\\log2\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}\\log2\\)",
      "\\(\\log2\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\log2\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "Using the King's property with \\(x=\\tan\\theta\\):\n\n\\(I=8\\int_0^{\\pi/4}\\log(1+\\tan\\theta)d\\theta\\)\n\nBy symmetry property: \\(I=8\\cdot\\dfrac{\\pi}{8}\\log2=\\pi\\log2\\)",
    "name": "King Property for Log Integral"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item6",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_{-\\pi/4}^{\\pi/4}x^3\\sin^4(x)\\,dx=\\)",
    "options": [
