      "\\(1\\)",
      "\\(2\\pi\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "\\(f(x)=x^3\\sin^4x\\). Since \\(f(-x)=(-x)^3\\sin^4(-x)=-x^3\\sin^4x=-f(x)\\), the function is **odd**.\n\n\\(\\int_{-\\pi/4}^{\\pi/4}x^3\\sin^4x\\,dx=0\\)",
    "name": "Odd Function on Symmetric Interval"
  },
  {
