    ],
    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "The integral simplifies to \\(\\dfrac{1}{2}\\int_0^1(1+t^4)dt=\\dfrac{1}{2}\\left[t+\\dfrac{t^5}{5}\\right]_0^1=\\dfrac{1}{2}\\cdot\\dfrac{6}{5}=\\dfrac{3}{5}\\).\n\nWait — from PDF: \\(I=\\int_0^1(1+t^4)dt=1+\\dfrac{1}{5}=\\dfrac{6}{5}\\).",
    "name": "Definite Integral via Power Substitution"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item8",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_{-1}^2|x|\\,dx=\\)",
