      "\\(2\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{5}{2}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{3}{2}\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "\\(\\int_{-1}^2|x|dx=\\int_{-1}^0(-x)dx+\\int_0^2x\\,dx=\\left[-\\dfrac{x^2}{2}\\right]_{-1}^0+\\left[\\dfrac{x^2}{2}\\right]_0^2=\\dfrac{1}{2}+2=\\dfrac{5}{2}\\)",
    "name": "Absolute Value Integral"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item9",
    "text": "If \\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^{b-c}f(x+c)\\,dx=k\\int_c^bf(x)\\,dx\\), then \\(k=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(1\\)",
      "\\(2\\)",
      "\\(0\\)",
      "\\(-2\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "Let \\(t=x+c\\), so when \\(x=0\\), \\(t=c\\) and when \\(x=b-c\\), \\(t=b\\):\n\n\\(\\int_c^bf(t)dt=k\\int_c^bf(x)dx\\implies k=1\\)",
    "name": "Substitution Property of Definite Integral"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item10",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^{\\pi/2}e^{\\sin x}\\cos x\\,dx=\\)",
    "options": [
