      "\\(-\\dfrac{3}{4}+2\\log2\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 3,
    "explanation": "By IBP: \\(\\int_0^1(1+x)\\log(1+x)dx\\)\n\n\\(=\\left[\\left(x+\\dfrac{x^2}{2}\\right)\\log(1+x)\\right]_0^1-\\int_0^1\\dfrac{x+x^2/2}{1+x}dx\\)\n\n\\(=\\dfrac{3}{2}\\log2-\\int_0^1\\dfrac{x}{2}dx=-\\dfrac{3}{4}+2\\log2\\)... From PDF: \\(=2\\log2-\\dfrac{3}{4}\\)",
    "name": "Integration by Parts"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item18",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_{\\pi/6}^{\\pi/3}\\frac{dx}{1+\\cot x}=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{12}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{6}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{13}\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "Using King's property with \\(a+b=\\pi/6+\\pi/3=\\pi/2\\):\n\n\\(I=\\int_{\\pi/6}^{\\pi/3}\\dfrac{\\sin x}{\\sin x+\\cos x}dx\\) and \\(I=\\int_{\\pi/6}^{\\pi/3}\\dfrac{\\cos x}{\\cos x+\\sin x}dx\\)\n\n\\(2I=\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}-\\dfrac{\\pi}{6}=\\dfrac{\\pi}{6}\\implies I=\\dfrac{\\pi}{12}\\)",
    "name": "King's Property Definite Integral"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item19",
    "text": "The value of \\(f(1)\\) given \\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^{x^2}t\\cdot f(t)\\,dt=x^5-x^3\\) is",
    "options": [
      "\\(4\\)",
      "\\(3\\)",
      "\\(2\\)",
      "\\(1\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 3,
    "explanation": "Differentiate both sides w.r.t. \\(x\\):\n\n\\(x^2\\cdot f(x^2)\\cdot2x=5x^4-3x^2\\implies2x^3f(x^2)=5x^4-3x^2\\)\n\nAt \\(x=1\\): \\(2f(1)=5-3=2\\implies f(1)=1\\)",
    "name": "Leibniz Rule for Differentiation Under Integral"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item20",
    "text": "If \\(I_1=\\displaystyle\\int_0^{\\pi/2}\\frac{x}{\\sin x}\\,dx\\) and \\(I_2=\\displaystyle\\int_0^1\\frac{\\tan^{-1}x}{x}\\,dx\\), then \\(I_1:I_2=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(1:1\\)",
      "\\(2:1\\)",
      "\\(3:1\\)",
      "\\(4:1\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 1,
    "explanation": "Let \\(t=\\tan^{-1}x\\) in \\(I_2\\):\n\n\\(I_2=\\int_0^{\\pi/4}\\dfrac{t}{\\tan t}\\sec^2t\\,dt=\\int_0^{\\pi/4}\\dfrac{t}{\\sin t\\cos t}dt=\\int_0^{\\pi/4}\\dfrac{2t}{\\sin2t}dt=\\dfrac{1}{2}\\int_0^{\\pi/2}\\dfrac{u}{\\sin u}du=\\dfrac{I_1}{2}\\)\n\nSo \\(I_1=2I_2\\implies I_1:I_2=2:1\\)",
    "name": "Ratio of Two Integrals"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item21",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^{\\pi/2}\\frac{x+\\sin x}{1+\\cos x}\\,dx=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{3}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{6}\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "\\(\\dfrac{x+\\sin x}{1+\\cos x}=\\dfrac{x}{2\\cos^2(x/2)}+\\dfrac{\\sin x}{1+\\cos x}=\\dfrac{x}{2}\\sec^2\\dfrac{x}{2}+\\tan\\dfrac{x}{2}\\)\n\nUsing \\(\\int(f'+xf)dx=xf(x)\\) form with \\(f=\\tan(x/2)\\):\n\n\\(=\\left[x\\tan\\dfrac{x}{2}\\right]_0^{\\pi/2}=\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}\\cdot1=\\dfrac{\\pi}{2}\\)",
    "name": "Integrand Decomposition"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item22",
    "text": "Area enclosed by \\(x^2=2-y\\) and \\(x^2=y\\) is",
    "options": [
      "\\(\\dfrac{2}{3}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{4}{3}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{8}{3}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{11}{3}\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 2,
    "explanation": "Intersection at \\(y=1\\), \\(x=\\pm1\\). Area:\n\n\\(A=2\\int_0^1\\left(\\sqrt{2-y}-\\sqrt{y}\\right)\\dfrac{dy}{2x}\\)... using horizontal integration:\n\n\\(A=\\int_{-1}^1[(2-x^2)-x^2]dx=\\int_{-1}^1(2-2x^2)dx=2\\left[x-\\dfrac{x^3}{3}\\right]_{-1}^1=2\\cdot\\dfrac{4}{3}=\\dfrac{8}{3}\\)",
    "name": "Area Between Two Parabolas"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item23",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^{\\pi/2}\\sin^4x\\cos^2x\\,dx=\\dfrac{\\pi}{32}\\). Then \\(\\displaystyle\\int_0^{\\pi/2}\\cos^4x\\sin^2x\\,dx=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{32}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{64}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{4}\\)",
      "\\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{8}\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 0,
    "explanation": "By King's property: \\(\\int_0^{\\pi/2}\\sin^4x\\cos^2x\\,dx=\\int_0^{\\pi/2}\\cos^4x\\sin^2x\\,dx\\).\n\nBoth equal \\(\\dfrac{\\pi}{32}\\).",
    "name": "Symmetry of Trigonometric Integral"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item24",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\int_{-a}^a\\sqrt{\\frac{a-x}{a+x}}\\,dx=\\)",
    "options": [
      "\\(\\dfrac{a\\pi}{2}\\)",
      "\\(1\\)",
      "\\(2a\\pi\\)",
      "\\(a\\pi\\)"
    ],
    "correctIndex": 3,
    "explanation": "Let \\(I=\\int_{-a}^a\\sqrt{\\dfrac{a-x}{a+x}}dx\\).\n\nAdding with its reflection: \\(2I=\\int_{-a}^a\\dfrac{2a}{\\sqrt{a^2-x^2}}dx=2a[\\sin^{-1}(x/a)]_{-a}^a=2a(\\pi)\\).\n\n\\(I=a\\pi\\)",
    "name": "Symmetric Integral Technique"
  },
  {
