    "explanation": "Intersection at \\(y=1\\). Total area \\(=2\\pi\\). Smaller part (under parabola):\n\n\\(\\text{Smaller}=\\pi+2\\int_0^1(\\sqrt{2-y}-\\sqrt{y})dy=\\pi+\\dfrac{2}{3}\\)\n\nLarger part \\(=2\\pi-\\left(\\pi+\\dfrac{2}{3}\\right)=\\dfrac{3\\pi}{2}-\\dfrac{1}{3}\\).",
    "name": "Area Split by Parabola and Circle"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item28",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\lim_{n\\to\\infty}\\left[\\frac{1}{n(n+1)}+\\frac{n^2}{(n+1)^3}+\\frac{n^2}{(n+2)^3}+\\cdots\\right]=\\)",
