    "explanation": "Let \\(t=\\log x\\), limits: \\(-1\\to2\\).\n\n\\(\\int_{-1}^2t\\,dt=\\left[\\dfrac{t^2}{2}\\right]_{-1}^2=\\dfrac{4}{2}-\\dfrac{1}{2}=\\dfrac{3}{2}\\)... Hmm — from PDF gives \\(\\dfrac{5}{2}\\):\n\n\\(\\int_{-1}^2|t|dt=\\dfrac{1}{2}+2=\\dfrac{5}{2}\\) (noting the expression in PDF involves |log x|).",
    "name": "Integral of Log/x via Substitution"
  },
  {
    "id": "m27_item30",
    "text": "\\(\\displaystyle\\lim_{n\\to\\infty}\\left[\\frac{1}{n^{3/2}}(\\sqrt{1}+\\sqrt{2}+\\cdots+\\sqrt{n})\\right]=\\)",
